body:
In Verilog-2001, support declaring modules this way was added:

```verilog
module Example
    #(PARAMETER = 0)
    (input clk);

    // Module code [...]
endmodule
```

Instead of:
```verilog
module Example(clk);
    parameter PARAMETER = 0;
    input clk;

    // Module code [...]
endmodule
```

However `iverilog` doesn't seem to support this.

code_blocks:
module Example
    #(PARAMETER = 0)
    (input clk);

    // Module code [...]
endmodule

module Example(clk);
    parameter PARAMETER = 0;
    input clk;

    // Module code [...]
endmodule
